<p>The <b>Slingbox</b> is a <a href="/wiki/TV" title="TV" class="mw-redirect">TV</a> <a href="/wiki/Streaming_media" title="Streaming media">streaming</a> device that enables users to remotely view their home's <a href="/wiki/Cable_television" title="Cable television">cable</a>, <a href="/wiki/Satellite_television" title="Satellite television">satellite</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Personal_video_recorder" title="Personal video recorder" class="mw-redirect">personal video recorder</a> (PVR) programming from an Internet-enabled computer with a <a href="/wiki/Broadband_Internet" title="Broadband Internet" class="mw-redirect">broadband Internet</a> connection. It is produced by <a href="/wiki/Sling_Media" title="Sling Media">Sling Media</a> of <a href="/wiki/San_Mateo,_California" title="San Mateo, California">San Mateo, California</a>.</p>
